Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled and finely diced). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Trim and quarter @zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered) lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Drain @cannellini beans{1%400g can}. Pick @thyme{1/4%ounce}(leaves picked) from stems; mince leaves until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings). Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped).

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{3%teaspoon} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir zucchini, beans, minced thyme, @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @mushroom stock concentrate{2}, 3 1/2 cups water (7 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} into pot.

Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer; cook, uncovered, until zucchini is just softened, ~{6-9%minutes}.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook, stirring frequently, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce} into pot. Cover and cook until couscous is tender, ~{7-9%minutes}. Taste and season generously with salt and pepper.

Once couscous is done, stir cooked chicken into soup.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Top with @crème fraîche{2%tablespoon}.

> TIP: Cut a corner of the crème fraîche pouch to create a piping bag!

Garnish with chopped parsley and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.